1.  **Its FREE for use by all**—donations are welcome from service providers;  

2.  **Available On-the-Go**—being a “mobile-first” Software-as-a-Service, e911 is fully accessible using the **mobile phone** (whether it is "features phone" or a smartphone) among other personal/portable electronic devices anywhere, anytime;  

3.  **Astoundingly cost effective to operate**—being a Software-as-a-Service, e911 does not require "dollars" consuming, very expensive IT infrastructure that are even more expensive to maintain, upgrade, secure and replace.  

4.  **Advances MULTIMEDIA communications**—e911 service can receive reports in various multimedia file format – **text, voice **(i.e. call, podcast, Voice Over Internet Protocol – VOIP), **photo, video, and LIVE-streaming**;  

5.  **Enables MULTICHANNEL (online-offline) communication**—via **ONLINE** (internet-driven) channels such as Instant messenger _(i.e. Telegram messenger, Facebook messenger, Skype messenger)_, Web, App, etc., and **OFFLINE** (non-internet driven) channels such as Short Messaging Service (SMS) or SmarText, Unstructured Supplementary Service Data (USSD) and SIM ToolKit;  

6.  **Capable of autonomous tracking of HELP request points**—using Global Position System (GPS) based tracking. _Only available for e911 HELP request made from smartphones with GPS tracking enabled_;  

7.  **Advances smart neighbourhood watch service and "I’m Safe!" notifications**—e911 technology provides for the set up of **neighbourhood eRegistry **and the **activation **of a **neighbourhood e911 ALERT/ALARM notification** in the event of an emergency. Members of a neighbourhood or family can send "I'm safe!" notification (emergency roll call) in the event of a natural disaster.  

8.  **InstantReport files: **Users of the service can create InstantReport files containing a profile of their home and car(s). This will enable the generation of precise, instant HELP request in the event of a burglary or car-snatch.
